The paper discusses the use of binary multilayer neural networks for image classification tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also focuses on the training of these networks using the Expectation BackPropagation algorithm, which is a technique commonly used in neural network optimization (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper explores the effectiveness of image spatial filters, which is a common technique in image processing (cs.CL). The use of dropout technique is also discussed, which is a regularization technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the binary neural networks on the MNIST dataset, which is a commonly used dataset in machine learning research (cs.AI).
